    \begin {tikzcd}
      & x\ar [dl, "\lambda _j"']\ar [dr, "\lambda _k"] \\
      Fj\ar [rr, "Ff"'] && Fk
    \end {tikzcd}


 commutes for each j\xrightarrow {f} k in J. This is exactly a cone
  over F with summit x, hence by the universal property of the
  limit, an element of the left-hand side.

Naturality of \eta  applied to u asserts that 




